title: Spain Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Spain Three Month Interbank Rate was at -0.38 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Spain averaged 3.07 percent from 1991 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 15.75 percent in March of 1993 and a record low of -0.40 percent in June of 2017. In Spain, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides the latest reported value for - Spain Three Month Interbank Rate - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Bank of Spain
